body:
@r-c-f By reproduce you mean you can not only get the clipboard to stop working, but it also starts working again once you switch between applications?

> The -vvv logs doesn't show anything when I select, and with events shown there's so much output I can't distinguish what's going on. I'll try to filter that out.

If someone can check the logs and grep for `clipboard` with at least warn and debug enabled, that might be helpful. There should be the errors `Unable to load text from clipboard` and `Unable to store text in clipboard` emitted when a store/load fails for some reason.
